2025-08-22 11:05:50,731 - INFO -     [特征生成] ["'new_feature': 'glucose_smoking_bmi_ratio'  \n'detailed description': This feature calculates the ratio of glucose levels to the product of average daily cigarette consumption and BMI. It aims to capture the combined effect of glucose levels, smoking habits, and BMI on the risk of coronary heart disease. High values may indicate a higher cardiovascular risk due to the interplay between these factors.  \n'brief description': A ratio combining glucose levels, smoking habits, and BMI to assess cardiovascular risk.  \n'relevant': ['glucose', 'cigsperday', 'bmi']", "'new_feature': 'glucose_pressure_ratio'\n\n'detailed description': The 'glucose_pressure_ratio' is calculated by taking the ratio of glucose level to the sum of systolic and diastolic blood pressure. This feature evaluates the interplay between blood sugar levels and blood pressure, aiding in the prediction of cardiovascular risks. High glucose levels alongside abnormal blood pressure readings can indicate heightened health risks.\n\n'brief description': A ratio of glucose level to the sum of systolic and diastolic blood pressure, indicating potential cardiovascular risk.\n\n'relevant': ['glucose', 'sysbp', 'diabp']", "'new_feature': 'cholesterol_bmi_interaction'\n'detailed description': This feature represents an interaction score between total cholesterol level and Body Mass Index (BMI), adjusted by whether the patient is currently on blood pressure medication and their smoking status. It is calculated by multiplying the total cholesterol level by the BMI, then adjusting it for patients on blood pressure medication or those who currently smoke.\n'brief description': Interaction score between cholesterol levels, BMI, and adjustment for blood pressure medication and smoking status.\n'relevant': ['totchol', 'bmi', 'bpmeds', 'currentsmoker']", "'new_feature': 'bmi_glucose_interaction_index'  \n'detailed description': This feature combines BMI and glucose levels to provide insights into the potential impact of obesity and blood sugar on cardiovascular risks. It is calculated by multiplying BMI with glucose levels and then adjusting for diabetes status, emphasizing the interaction between body mass and metabolic factors.  \n'brief description': Interaction index between BMI and glucose, adjusted for diabetes.  \n'relevant': ['bmi', 'glucose', 'diabetes']  ", "'new_feature': 'exercise_cholesterol_interaction_score'  \n'detailed description': This feature quantifies the interaction between a patient's physical activity level and their cholesterol levels, adjusted by blood pressure medications and heart rate. This score aims to provide insights into how lifestyle choices and medical interventions impact cholesterol management, ultimately influencing cardiovascular health.  \n'brief description': Interaction score between exercise habits, cholesterol levels, blood pressure medication, and heart rate.  \n'relevant': ['totchol', 'bpmeds', 'heartrate']  ", "'new_feature': 'age_blood_pressure_interaction_score'  \n'detailed description': This new feature is an interaction score combining age, systolic blood pressure (sysbp), and diastolic blood pressure (diabp). It is designed to assess the compounded effect of age and blood pressure levels on cardiovascular risk, as both age and high blood pressure are significant risk factors for coronary heart disease.  \n'brief description': An interaction score combining age and blood pressure levels to assess cardiovascular risk.  \n'relevant': ['age', 'sysbp', 'diabp']  ", "'new_feature': 'smoking_education_impact_score'  \n'detailed description': This feature is a composite score that combines the level of education and smoking habits (both current smoking status and average cigarettes per day) to estimate the potential socio-behavioral impact on health risks. Education level often correlates with health literacy, which can influence lifestyle choices such as smoking. The feature is calculated by normalizing the education level and multiplying it by a factor derived from the smoking status and average cigarettes per day, indicating a potential education-modulated impact of smoking on health.  \n'brief description': Composite score combining education level and smoking habits to evaluate socio-behavioral impact on health risks.  \n'relevant': ['education', 'currentsmoker', 'cigsperday']  ", "'new_feature': 'cholesterol_heart_rate_ratio'  \n'detailed description': This new feature represents the ratio of total cholesterol to heart rate, providing an insight into the balance between lipid levels and cardiac activity. A higher ratio might indicate either high cholesterol or low heart rate, both of which can signify potential cardiac risk. Understanding this balance can help in predicting the risk of coronary heart disease.  \n'brief description': Ratio of total cholesterol to heart rate for assessing cardiac risk.  \n'relevant': ['totchol', 'heartrate']", "'new_feature': 'bmi_glucose_interaction_score'  \n'detailed description': This feature captures the interaction between Body Mass Index (BMI) and glucose levels, providing an integrated measure of metabolic health. It assesses how the body mass and glucose levels correlate to impact the risk of health issues like heart disease.  \n'brief description': An interaction score between BMI and glucose levels.  \n'relevant': ['bmi', 'glucose']", "{'new_feature': 'cardiovascular_load_index'}\n'detailed description': The 'cardiovascular_load_index' is a composite feature that assesses the impact of the heart's workload related to hypertension and tobacco influence. It is calculated as the product of systolic blood pressure (sysbp), current smoking status (currentsmoker), and heart rate (heartrate), adjusted by the education level, reflecting the role of lifestyle and knowledge on cardiovascular health.\n'brief description': An index evaluating cardiovascular stress from blood pressure, smoking, and heart rate, adjusted by education.\n'relevant': ['sysbp', 'currentsmoker', 'heartrate', 'education']", "'new_feature': 'glucose_bmi_smoking_correlation'  \n'detailed description': A new feature that evaluates the correlation between glucose levels, BMI, and smoking habits. This feature is computed by multiplying glucose level, BMI, and an indicator of smoking status, thereby assessing the combined effect of these factors on potential health risks.  \n'brief description': A combined measure of glucose, BMI, and smoking risk.  \n'relevant': ['glucose', 'bmi', 'currentsmoker']", "'new_feature': 'education_bmi_interaction_score'  \n'detailed description': This feature quantifies the interaction between education level and body mass index (BMI). It is calculated by multiplying the encoded education level by the BMI of the patient. This feature aims to capture the combined impact of education level and BMI on health, particularly in relation to the risk of coronary heart disease.  \n'brief description': Interaction score between education level and BMI.  \n'relevant': ['education', 'bmi']  "]
