sk factors for cardiovascular diseases.  \n'brief description': An index combining cholesterol, smoking, and blood pressure to assess cardiovascular risk.  \n'relevant': ['totchol', 'currentsmoker', 'cigsperday', 'sysbp']", "'new_feature': 'chol_glucose_impact_ratio'  \n'detailed description': This feature calculates the ratio of total cholesterol to glucose levels, adjusted by the presence of diabetes and smoking habits. It aims to evaluate the combined impact of cholesterol and glucose management on overall health, considering the added risk factors of smoking and diabetes.  \n'brief description': A ratio assessing the impact of cholesterol and glucose, influenced by smoking and diabetes risks.  \n'relevant': ['totchol', 'glucose', 'diabetes', 'currentsmoker']", "'new_feature': 'gender_education_interaction_index',\n'detailed description': 'This feature is created by interacting the gender and education level to assess how gender-specific education impacts health risk factors and the potential for coronary heart disease. It considers gender differences in lifestyle, awareness, and preventive health measures influenced by education.',\n'brief description': 'An index measuring the interaction between gender and education level in relation to health risks.',\n'relevant': ['gender', 'education']", "'new_feature': 'cholesterol_smoke_diabetes_interaction'  \n'detailed description': This feature is calculated by taking the product of total cholesterol (totchol), an indicator for being a current smoker (currentsmoker), and an indicator for diabetes (diabetes). It aims to encapsulate the combined effect of cholesterol levels, smoking habits, and diabetes status on cardiovascular health risk.  \n'brief description': A feature combining total cholesterol, smoking status, and diabetes to evaluate cardiovascular risk.  \n'relevant': ['totchol', 'currentsmoker', 'diabetes']  ", "'new_feature': 'heart_health_impact_score'  \n'detailed description': This score evaluates the impact of heart health on the risk of coronary heart disease. It is calculated by considering heart rate, total cholesterol, and the presence of diabetes. An elevated heart rate and high cholesterol levels can indicate poor heart health, which is further compounded by diabetes. The formula is: (heartrate * totchol) / (1 + diabetes).  \n'brief description': A score assessing heart health impact on coronary heart disease risk, considering heart rate, cholesterol, and diabetes.  \n'relevant': ['heartrate', 'totchol', 'diabetes']", "'new_feature': 'diabetes_smoking_risk_index'  \n'detailed description': This feature combines the presence of diabetes, smoking status, and blood pressure levels to assess the overall risk of cardiovascular disease. It is calculated by taking the product of the diabetes indicator, current smoker status, and systolic blood pressure. The rationale is that individuals with both diabetes and smoking habits are at an increased risk, which is further exacerbated by high blood pressure.  \n'brief description': A risk index for cardiovascular disease based on diabetes, smoking status, and blood pressure.  \n'relevant': ['diabetes', 'currentsmoker', 'sysbp']", "'new_feature': 'education_smoking_interaction_score'  \n'detailed description': This feature evaluates the interaction between education level and smoking habits by considering the education level and adjusting for the average number of cigarettes smoked per day. It aims to capture how different levels of education influence smoking behavior and its potential effects on health outcomes, particularly cardiovascular disease.  \n'brief description': An interaction score between education level and smoking habits.  \n'relevant': ['education', 'currentsmoker', 'cigsperday']", "'new_feature': 'age_bmi_smoker_interaction',\n'detailed description': This feature combines age, BMI, and smoking status to quantify the interaction between a patient's age, their Body Mass Index (BMI), and their smoking habits. I