oronary heart disease risk. It aims to capture the synergistic effect of these conditions, adjusted by age and gender.\n'brief description': Interaction score combining previous stroke history and hypertension status.\n'relevant': ['gender', 'age', 'prevalentstroke', 'prevalenthyp']", "'new_feature': 'smoking_cardiovascular_index'  \n'detailed description': The smoking cardiovascular index is a composite score derived from combining smoking habits (currentsmoker and cigsperday) with cardiovascular risk factors (age, sysbp, diabp, glucose, and cholesterol levels). It evaluates the potential impact of smoking on cardiovascular health, considering the cumulative effect of these attributes.  \n'brief description': A composite score assessing the impact of smoking on cardiovascular health.  \n'relevant': ['currentsmoker', 'cigsperday', 'age', 'sysbp', 'diabp', 'glucose', 'totchol']", "\n'new_feature': 'smoking_impact_index'\n'detailed description': This feature combines the patient's smoking status, number of cigarettes per day, and any prevalent health conditions like stroke, hypertension, diabetes along with their age and gender. It aims to quantify the impact of smoking on overall health, considering both the frequency of smoking and existing health conditions.\n'brief description': A composite index evaluating the impact of smoking on health, considering frequency, existing conditions, age, and gender.\n'relevant': ['currentsmoker', 'cigsperday', 'prevalentstroke', 'prevalenthyp', 'diabetes', 'age', 'gender']", "'new_feature': 'smoking_glucose_bmi_impact'\n'detailed description': This feature calculates the impact of smoking habits, glucose levels, and BMI on cardiovascular risk. It is created by combining smoking status, glucose levels, and BMI values, adjusted by the number of cigarettes smoked per day. High glucose levels can indicate increased risk of cardiovascular issues, and smoking exacerbates this risk, especially in individuals with higher BMI.\n'brief description': Impact of smoking, glucose levels, and BMI on cardiovascular risk.\n'relevant': ['currentsmoker', 'cigsperday', 'glucose', 'bmi']", "'new_feature': 'stroke_diabetes_pressure_index'  \n'detailed description': This index evaluates the combined risk of stroke and diabetes by considering systolic and diastolic blood pressure measurements and the presence of previous stroke incidents. It is calculated as the product of systolic blood pressure, diastolic blood pressure, and binary indicators for diabetes and prevalent stroke.  \n'brief description': A composite index assessing stroke and diabetes risk based on blood pressure measurements and previous stroke incidents.  \n'relevant': ['sysbp', 'diabp', 'diabetes', 'prevalentstroke']", "'new_feature': 'activity_pressure_interaction_score'\n'detailed description': This feature quantifies the interaction between physical activity, represented by heart rate, and blood pressure metrics (sysbp and diabp). It considers how heart rate changes might impact blood pressure values, which is crucial for cardiovascular health risk evaluation, especially in patients with a history of stroke or hypertension.\n'brief description': Interaction score between heart rate and blood pressure.\n'relevant': ['heartrate', 'sysbp', 'diabp', 'prevalentstroke', 'prevalenthyp']", "'new_feature': 'age_smoking_glucose_interaction'\n'detailed description': This feature captures the interaction between age, smoking habits, and glucose levels, highlighting the compounding effect of aging, smoking, and glucose levels on cardiovascular health. It is calculated as the product of standardized age, number of cigarettes smoked per day, and glucose level.\n'brief description': Interaction of age, smoking, and glucose levels impacting cardiovascular health.\n'relevant': ['age', 'cigsperday', 'glucose']", "'new_feature': 'smoking_pressure_impact_index'\n'detailed description': This feature captures the interaction between smoking habits and blood pressure, factoring in the number of cigarettes smoked per day and both systolic and diastolic blood pressure levels. It reflects how smoking may intensify blood pressure issues, which is crucial for assessing heart disease risks.\n'brief description': Interaction score between smoking intensity and blood pressure levels.\n'relevant': ['currentsmoker', 'cigsperday', 'sysbp', 'diabp']", "'new_feature': 'age_blood_pressure_interaction'\n'detailed description': This feature calculates the interaction between age and blood pressure, specifically by taking the product of age, systolic blood pressure (sysbp), and diastolic blood pressure (diabp). This interaction is significant as it can help evaluate the joint impact of age and blood pressure levels on cardiovascular health risks, considering that both factors are crucial indicators of heart disease risk.\n'brief description': Interaction feature between age and blood pressure levels.\n'relevant': ['age', 'sysbp', 'diabp']"]
