ly related to blood pressure management.  \n'brief description': Interaction score combining cholesterol and blood pressure levels, adjusted for diabetes and smoking.  \n'relevant': ['totchol', 'sysbp', 'diabp', 'diabetes', 'currentsmoker']  ", "'new_feature': 'smoking_cardiovascular_interaction_index'\n'detailed description': This feature combines the impact of smoking habits, represented by the number of cigarettes smoked per day, with the cardiovascular risk factors like systolic and diastolic blood pressure and glucose levels. It reflects how smoking intensity may interact with physiological parameters that are crucial for cardiovascular health.\n'brief description': Interaction index reflecting the combined effects of smoking habits and cardiovascular health indicators.\n'relevant': ['cigsperday', 'sysbp', 'diabp', 'glucose']", "'new_feature': 'glucose_bp_impact_ratio'  \n'detailed description': This feature calculates the ratio of glucose levels to a weighted sum of systolic and diastolic blood pressure, providing insight into how blood sugar levels may impact cardiovascular health, especially under varying blood pressure conditions.  \n'brief description': Ratio of glucose levels to combined blood pressure impact.  \n'relevant': [glucose, sysbp, diabp]", "'new_feature': 'glucose_smoking_interaction_index'\n'detailed description': This feature measures the interaction between smoking habits and glucose levels. It combines glucose levels with the presence of smoking behaviors and is adjusted for blood pressure medication usage. The feature aims to capture how smoking and glucose levels jointly impact cardiovascular health and disease risk.\n'brief description': Interaction index between smoking habits and glucose levels.\n'relevant': ['glucose', 'currentsmoker', 'bpmeds']", "'new_feature': 'activity_health_index'  \n'detailed description': A composite score that combines heart rate and education levels to assess overall activity health. Heart rate is often an indicator of cardiovascular fitness, and education level is associated with health awareness and lifestyle choices. This feature aims to capture the impact of physical activity levels and health literacy on overall health.  \n'brief description': A measure combining heart rate and education to evaluate activity health.  \n'relevant': ['heartrate', 'education']", "'new_feature': 'exercise_cardiovascular_impact'  \n'detailed description': This feature evaluates the impact of physical activity on cardiovascular health by integrating heart rate, BMI, and education level. It aims to identify how lifestyle factors, especially exercise and general knowledge (represented by education), affect cardiovascular outcomes.  \n'brief description': Measures the effect of exercise, BMI, and education on cardiovascular health.  \n'relevant': ['heartrate', 'bmi', 'education']", "'new_feature': 'age_blood_pressure_glucose_interaction'\n'detailed description': This feature is an interaction score calculated by multiplying age, systolic and diastolic blood pressure, and glucose levels. It reflects the compounded effects of age and cardiovascular risks on glucose metabolism.\n'brief description': Interaction score combining age, blood pressure, and glucose levels for enhanced cardiovascular risk prediction.\n'relevant': ['age', 'sysbp', 'diabp', 'glucose']", "'new_feature': 'pressure_glucose_ratio'  \n'detailed description': The pressure_glucose_ratio combines systolic and diastolic blood pressure levels with glucose levels to assess the impact of blood pressure on glucose management. It considers the potential influence of blood pressure medication on glucose regulation and overall cardiovascular health.  \n'brief description': A ratio analyzing the interplay between blood pressure and glucose levels.  \n'relevant': ['bpmeds', 'sysbp', 'diabp', 'glucose']", "'new_feature': 'bmi_pressure_impact_score'  \n'detailed description': This feature evaluates the combined impact of BMI and blood pressure on individual health. It is calculated by multiplying the BMI with the sum of systolic and diastolic blood pressure, incorporating the interaction effects of these physical health indicators.  \n'brief description': Combined impact of BMI with blood pressure indicators.  \n'relevant': ['bmi', 'sysbp', 'diabp']"]
